@node cc "CLI Colour selector - CColour"

 Usage:

 > cc <bg> <fg>

 bg is the background colour and
 fg is the foreground colour.

 The values you enter must be within the range 0-7.

@endnode

@node cs "CLI Scroller..."

 Usage:

 > cs <text> <text> ...

 Text is simply the text you want to scroll.

 Example:

 > cs No RISC - No fun!

 Will scroll that text from the right to the left.

@endnode

@node st "SetRGB32"

 SetRGB32 is just a Shell version of the graphics.library SetRGB32()
 function.

 Usage:

 > SetRGB32 <reg> <r> <g> <b>

 reg is the colour register you want to alter.
 r is the red value (0-255)
 g is the green value (0-255)
 b is the blue value (0-255)

 Example:

 > SetRGB32 0 145 145 130

 This will make the background colour a bit more yellow...

@endnode

@node li "Libs"

 Usage:

 Just type libs, and you'll get a list of all libraries in memory.

@endnode
